.TH "vmw_surface_dma_encode" 9 "vmw_surface_dma_encode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_surface_dma_encode \- Encode a surface_dma command.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_surface_dma_encode
.BI "(struct vmw_surface *srf "  ","
.BI "void *cmd_space "  ","
.BI "const SVGAGuestPtr *ptr "  ","
.BI "bool to_surface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "srf" 12
Pointer to a struct vmw_surface object.
.IP "cmd_space" 12
Pointer to memory area in which the commands should be encoded.
.IP "ptr" 12
Pointer to an SVGAGuestPtr indicating where the surface contents
should be placed or read from.
.IP "to_surface" 12
Boolean whether to DMA to the surface or from the surface.
